SIMPLE: horary
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Horary
<hw>Ho"ra*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>horarius</ets>, fr. L. <ets>hora</ets> hour: cf. F.
<ets>horaire</ets>. See <er>Hour</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or
pertaining to an hour; noting the hours.</def>
<rj><au>Spectator.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Occurring once an hour; continuing an hour; hourly;
ephemeral.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Horary</qex>, or soon decaying, fruits of summer.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir T. Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Horary circles</b></col>. <cd>See
<er>Circles</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Horatian</ent>⟦br⟧
